  "texts": [
    "This trend suggests that seeing more constraints helps the model better differentiate between correct and corrupted constraints.",
    "4.4 LLM judges are unreliable for evaluating constraint satisfaction in long-form generation.",
    "We experiment with using LLMs to evaluate whether texts generated by our fine-tuned models follow the given constraints.",
    "Specifically, we provide GPT-4o (OpenAI, 2024), Gemini-1.5-Pro (Team et al., 2024), and Claude-3.5-Sonnet (Anthropic, 2024) with a constraint and a generated text from our models and prompt it to determine whether the text fully satisfies, partially satisfies, or does not satisfy the constraint (Table 16).",
    "12 We then compare these results with judgments from three Upwork annotators on 30 texts generated by Suri-SFT on the test set (obtained using the same procedure as in Section 2.3)."
  ],
